-- Czech Stocks: Telefonica Czech, New World Resources Are Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-16T15:42:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/czech-stocks-telefonica-czech-new-world-resources-are-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
slid 0.3 percent to 901.40 at the end of trading in Prague.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, climbed the most this month, rising 1.3 percent
to 102.29 koruna.  Europe ’s benchmark coal derivatives jumped 0.9
percent to $97.20 a metric ton in the Netherlands.  Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT)   rose 0.5 percent to
392.2 koruna. The country’s biggest phone company was raised to
neutral from underweight at JPMorgan Chase & Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  